The paper deals with modeling and analyzing trial-offer markets with social influence and position bias. The paper's focus on market dynamics, equilibrium, and efficiency suggests that it belongs to the Game Theory (cs.GT) sub-category. The use of social influence and position bias in the model suggests that it also belongs to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category. The paper's use of simulations and agent-based models suggests that it may also belong to the Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) sub-category. The paper's focus on market efficiency and control suggests that it may also belong to the Computational Economics and Finance (cs.CE) sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on market dynamics and equilibrium suggests that it may also belong to the Electronic Commerce (cs.EC) sub-category.
